{{Infobox Software | name = All My Movies | logo = Amm logo120.png | screenshot = | caption = | collapsible = | author = | developer = Bolide Software | released = {{Start date and age|2003|08|21}} | latest release version = 8.9 build 1455 | latest release date = {{Start date and age|2018|05|27}} | latest preview version = | latest preview date = | operating system = Microsoft Windows | platform = | size = | language = English, Dutch, Finnish, French, German, Italian, Polish, Russian, Spanish | status = | genre = [[Digital asset management]] | license = [[Trialware]] | website = {{URL|bolidesoft.com}} }}
'''All My Movies''' is a movie collection organizer software for establishing a personal database of media collections ([[Blu-ray Disc]]s, [[DVD]]s, [[VHS| VHS tapes]], etc.) developed by Bolide Software.
Initially developed by Max Smirnoff (now Bolide Software [[Chief executive officer|CEO]]) for his personal usage, the program was published on Bolide Software web site as a [[shareware]]. All My Movies uses [[Amazon Web Services]] and a dozen of other [[Application programming interface|APIs]] provided by the online movie databases for automatical movie details retrieval. It supports almost any [[Barcode reader]] including the cheap [[CueCat]] for a fast movie lookup.
==See also== *[[Delicious Library]] *[[DVDpedia]] *[[DVD Profiler]]
