{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Appletons''' travel guides}}
[[Image:1873 Appletons Hand Book of American Travel Southern Tour.png|thumb|right|''Appletons' Hand-Book of American Travel: Southern Tour'', 1873]]
[[File:Appleton's Railway and Steam Navigation Guide - December, 1870.jpg|thumb|right|''Appletons' Railway & Steam Navigation Guide'', December 1870]]
'''''Appletons'''''' travel [[guide book]]s were published by [[D. Appleton & Company]] of New York.<ref>{{cite book |title=Appletons' Guide-Book to Alaska |chapter=Appleton's Guide-Books |chapterurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=i4t-eao3nacC&pg=PA162 |year=1893|publisher=D. Appleton and Co.}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |journal=Literary Era |location=Philadelphia |year=1896 |title=Appletons' Guides |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=3TDZAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA91 }}</ref> The firm's series of guides to railway travel in the United States began in the 1840s. Soon after it issued additional series of handbooks for tourists in the United States, Europe, Canada and Latin America.<ref name=cocks2001>{{Citation |publisher = University of California Press |isbn = 0520227468 |publication-place = Berkeley |title = Doing the Town: the Rise of Urban Tourism in the United States, 1850-1915 |author = Catherine Cocks |publication-date = 2001 }}</ref>

