'''Asia Book of Records''' is [[world record]] registrar organisation. Asia book of records register human achievement and natural events for individual and institutions based in the [[Asian countries|Asian]] countries.<ref>[http://www.daijiworld.com/news/news_disp.asp?n_id=266958 "Mangalore: KMC enters Asia Book of Records with largest heartbeat simulation"]</ref><ref> {{cite news | title = On a record drive, again | author = | publisher = [[The Hindu]] | url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/on-a-record-drive-again/article6965806.ece | date = March 6, 2015 }}</ref><ref> {{cite news | title = KMC enters Asia Book of Records with largest heartbeat simulation | author = | publisher = Daiji World | url = http://www.daijiworld.com/news/news_disp.asp?n_id=266958 | date = September 28, 2014 }}</ref><ref> {{cite news | title = Assam: Lamp burning for 484 years enters Asia Book of Records | author = | publisher = [[Press Trust of India]] | url = http://ibnlive.in.com/news/assam-lamp-burning-for-484-years-enters-asia-book-of-records/283845-3-251.html | date = Aug 20, 2012 }}</ref>
